The paper presents a new neural network architecture that is designed to improve the efficiency of deep neural networks. The focus is on convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the advantages of the proposed architecture in terms of parameter efficiency and computation complexity, which suggests that it could be relevant to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper proposes a new building block for CNNs, which could be of interest to researchers in the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
